Reasoning: The paper discusses a hybrid static/dynamic scheduling strategy for direct methods used in dense numerical linear algebra, which involves optimizing the computation of LU factorization. This falls under the category of parallel and distributed computing (cs.DC) and numerical analysis (cs.NA). The paper also discusses load balancing and data locality, which are important topics in parallel computing (cs.PF) and scientific computing (cs.SC). Finally, the paper presents experimental results and performance comparisons with other libraries, which could fall under the category of performance evaluation (cs.MS).
